\begin{pmatrix} x' \\ y' \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} \cos\theta & -\sin\theta \\ \sin\theta & \cos\theta \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix}
P(x,y)=x^2-xy+y^2=5
\theta=-45^{\circ}
-\pi/4
(x,y)
x' = \frac{x+y}{\sqrt{2}}, \quad y'=\frac{y-x}{\sqrt{2}},
\cos(-45^{\circ})=1/{\sqrt{2}}
\sin(-45^{\circ})=-1/\sqrt{2}
 P(x',y') = (x')^2 - x'y'+(y')^2=5 
\left(\frac{x+y}{\sqrt{2}}\right)^2 - \left(\frac{x+y}{\sqrt{2}}\right)\left(\frac{y-x}{\sqrt{2}}\right)+\left(\frac{y-x}{\sqrt{2}}\right)^2=5 
 \frac{x^2+2xy+y^2}{2}-\frac{y^2-x^2}{2}+\frac{y^2-2xy+x^2}{2}=5, 
 3x^2+y^2=10.
\{x',y'\}
P(x',y')=5
\{(x,y):3x^2+y^2=10\}
45^{\circ}
